{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"REBAR-DEBUG DIAGNOSIS (2026-07-21)\n\nReproduced on current origin/main with rebar metrics --output json: attempts_per_ticket, rework_within_7_days, revert_recovery, reopen_recovery, first_pass_rate, cost_per_accepted_change, env_diagnosis_intervals, and first_pass_verification all render unavailable with reason \"Invalid isoformat string: ''\".\n\nRoot cause: src/rebar/_commands/metrics.py normalizes absent or empty --since/--until to empty strings, places them in the context, and fault-isolates each resulting reader exception. src/rebar/metrics/event_metrics.py _bounds treats every non-None value as parseable and calls datetime.fromisoformat(\"\"). Git readers independently tolerate empty values, producing the inconsistent partial report. Fault isolation masks the boundary contract violation as metric unavailability.\n\nMinimal corrective seam: normalize the default window once in metrics_cli to concrete ISO dates for today and today-30d, make explicit blank values follow the same rule, keep reader functions defensive, update help/docs, and add a no-flags interface regression that asserts real ticket-derived values and the reported output bounds.\n\nNo code changed during this diagnostic run."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784653321542611001,"uuid":"bda86e34-3f4d-40ac-a4b4-f2d81ad610be"}